      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>10-Bromo-<i>α</i>-chamigrene, a compound isolated from marine algae, is thought to be biosynthesized from <i>γ</i>-bisabolene by the following route:</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbllTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--0d44bd9531650fe07a00ad87c3eb5ce97d7c9325/OChem_08_EC_025.jpg\" alt=\"A 3-step reaction shows the formation of 10-bromo-alpha-chamigrene from gamma-bisabolene.\">\n<p>Draw the structures of the intermediate bromonium and cyclic carbocation, and propose mechanisms for all three steps.</p>",
